Secure SMTP Relay & Reverse Proxy-based WAF
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Configure secure SMTP relay with authentication and TLS encryption
Implement firewall rules and fail2ban protection for SMTP services
Deploy Nginx as a reverse proxy-based Web Application Firewall (WAF)
Create custom WAF rules to detect and block common web attacks
Develop Python automation scripts for WAF rule management
Analyze security logs to identify attack patterns
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of SMTP, HTTP/HTTPS protocols
Familiarity with firewall concepts
Basic Python programming skills
Knowledge of common web vulnerabilities (SQL injection, XSS)
