Troubleshooting Tips
SMTP Issues:

If Postfix fails to start, check configuration: sudo postfix check
Verify SASL database permissions: ls -l /etc/sasldb2
Test authentication: testsaslauthd -u testuser -p password
Nginx/WAF Issues:

Configuration errors: sudo nginx -t shows syntax problems
Rules not blocking: Check if WAF rules are included in virtual host
Rate limiting not working: Verify zone definitions in waf-rules.conf
Python Script Issues:

Import errors: Ensure virtual environment is activated
Permission denied: Run script with sudo or adjust file permissions
Nginx reload fails: Check if user has sudo privileges for systemctl
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated implementing defense-in-depth security by combining SMTP relay protection with a reverse proxy-based WAF. Students configured multiple security layers including authentication, encryption, firewall rules, and application-level filtering. The Python automation component enables continuous security updates through threat intelligence integration. These skills are essential for securing modern infrastructure against email-based attacks and web application exploits.

Key Takeaways:

Multi-layered security provides better protection than single solutions
Automation is critical for maintaining current threat intelligence
Log analysis helps identify attack patterns and improve defenses
Rate limiting prevents resource exhaustion and brute force attacks
